al [38;2;139;127;119m· [38;2;255;176;32m5 warn [38;2;139;127;119m· 1 info[K\r[m\n  [38;2;226;61;45mCRITICAL [mGateway auth missing on loopback[K\r\n    gateway.bind is loopback but no gateway auth secret is configured. If the Control UI is exposed through a reverse pr\r\n[29;120Hroxy, unauthenticated access is possible.\r\n    [38;2;139;127;119mFix: Set gateway.auth (token recommended) or keep the Control UI local-only.\r[m\n  [38;2;255;176;32mWARN [mReverse proxy headers are not trusted[K\r\n    gateway.bind is loopback and gateway.trustedProxies is empty. If you expose the Control UI through a reverse proxy, \r\n[29;120H configure trusted proxies so local-client c…\r\n    [38;2;139;127;119mFix: Set gateway.trustedProxies to your proxy IPs or keep the Control UI local-only.[K\r[m\n  [38;2;255;176;32mWARN [mFeishu doc create can grant requester permissions[K\r\n    channels.feishu tools include \"doc\"; feishu_doc action \"create\" can grant document access to the trusted requesting \r\n[29;120H Feishu user.\r\n    [38;2;139;127;119mFix: Disable channels.feishu.tools.doc when not needed, and restrict tool access for untrusted prompts.[K\r[m\n  [38;2;255;176;32mWARN [mGateway HTTP APIs are reachable without auth[K\r\n    gateway.auth.mode=\"none\" leaves /tools/invoke callable without a shared secret. Treat this as trusted-local only and\r\n[29;120Hd avoid exposing the gateway beyond loopback.\r\n    [38;2;139;127;119mFix: Set gateway.auth.mode to token/password (recommended). If you intentionally keep mode=none, keep gateway.bind=l[m\r\n[38;2;139;127;119m[29;120Hloopback and disable optional HTTP endpoints.\r[m\n  [38;2;255;176;32mWARN [mExtensions exist but plugins.allow is not set[K\r\n    Found 1 extension(s) under C:\\Users\\Administrator\\.openclaw\\extensions. Without plugins.allow, any discovered plugin\r\n[29;120Hn id may load (depending on config and plugi…\r\n    [38;2;139;127;119mFix: Set plugins.allow to an explicit list of plugin ids you trust.[K\r[m\n 